               <p>JOHN WREN. I am a shopman to Mr. John Oldchurch Webb - he lives in the <rs id="t18340220-187-viclabel1076" type="occupation">Strand</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340220-187-victim1767 t18340220-187-viclabel1076"></join> - on the 17th of February, about six o'clock in the evening, the trousers were hanging at the door - the prisoner was seen to be looking at them, and he ran off with them - Carlisle and I pursued him - he was stopped near Covent-garden - in coming back we found the trousers in Bedford-street, in the way he had run.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340220-187-person1768">
                  RICHARD 
                  CARLISLE
               <interp inst="t18340220-187-person1768" type="surname" value="CARLISLE"></interp>
